This place is very clean, and the staff is friendly. However, some more training might be in order. When I got there this morning, the order I had placed last night by phone had been neglected,; they had a handwritten slip of paper with my order, but nobody had started it, so they had to create my order on the fly. This delayed me for about 10 minutes, not horrible but kind of annoying. Also, one of the big boxes of coffee did not get assembled well, and they did not check it before giving it to me. When I get to my car, I noticed that it was about to collapse. I took it back in, and after some fussing, they put the bag of hot coffee into a new box. They also did not label which was regular and which was decaf. Take-away: if it's anything complicated, be very clear with the staff as to what you need, and be prepared to wait. But they are kind people.
